1) Click "+" to add a plot to your graph 2) In the new window that appears, click "..." to select csv 3) Once loaded, select the correct columns for your domain and range from the dropdowns. 4) Fill out the rest of the fields as you see fit and click "Add Plot". The plot will be listed below. 5) If you make a mistake or would like to remove a plot you've added, select it with your mouse & click "-". 6) When you've added at least one plot and are readty to create your graph, click on GraphIt!
** The first plot you add will define the domain and range for all other plots, regardless of what you set them to. ** Design will reflect this eventually, but this is expected behaviour. Make sure to plot the data w/ the largest ** domain and range first. If you would like this behaviour to change, contact david@jdc.tech with your ideas.
